FBIS3-10980 "drlat051_a_94009" FBIS-LAT-94-051 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Mar 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Nation To Go on `Summer Time' on 2 Apr FL1603010694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2039 GMT 15 Mar 94 FL1603010694 Havana Radio Reloj Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] The Electric Union of the Ministry of Basic Industry has announced that summer time will go into effect throughout Cuba on 2 April at midnight, at which time clocks will be set forward one hour. The main objective of this traditional measure is to take maximum advantage of the light of the sun. Official time will be reestablished on 9 October, at 0100, at which time clocks will be set back 60 minutes.
